value.value: Delirios de infestación

definition.value: A persistent belief that a person is infested with living or non-living pathogens, such as parasites, insects, or bugs, when no such infestation is present.
This may occur in conjunction with tactile hallucinations of bugs or insects crawling on one's skin and is related to substance use disorders (delirium tremens).

value.value: Atmósfera delirante

definition.value: A persistent sense or a hunch that something is different in an imperceptible manner. Typically the perception is one of a sinister, portentous , uncanny, mysterious, or peculiar sense of foreboding in an indefinable way. There is an innate sense of inexplicable self-relevance to the person. There is often a feeling of anticipation, sometimes even excitement, that soon the mystery may be revealed and all the separate parts of their experience will fit together to reveal something immensely significant. The duration of this experience may vary, lasting from hours to days. It may be intermittent over an extended period of time (months to years).

value.value: Identificación errónea delirante

definition.value: A group of complex, monothematic delusional phenomena in which subjects hold a belief that the identity of a familiar person, object, location, or self has been altered or replaced. The majority of misidentifications are spouses or first degree relatives, i.e. someone well-known to the person.

value.value: Delirio religioso

definition.value: Delusions with a religious content that are considered delusional in nature based on how the belief is held and the evidence offered to support it, which is generally considered impossible or fantastical in the cultural setting of the person. It differs from unusual beliefs that are held with tenacity or conviction and are typically associated with other phenomena consistent with mental illness.

value.value: Patrón psicótico anormal

definition.value: Any abnormal pattern of psychotic experiences, where an individual has significant disturbances in their thoughts, perceptions, emotions, and behavior, resulting in a loss of touch with reality.

value.value: Labio hendido unilateral incompleto
不完全片側口唇裂
Unilateral cleft lip cleft that starts from the bottom of the upper lip but does not reach the nasal cavity.

definition.value: Please use this term only when the cleft lip is unilateral, ie occurring only on one side.

value.value: Labio hendido unilateral completo
完全な片側口唇裂
Unilateral cleft lip cleft that starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity.

definition.value: Please use this term only when the cleft lip is unilateral, ie occurring only on one side.

value.value: Microforma de labio hendido unilateral
微形片側口唇裂
Notch, groove, or scar of the upper lip without noticeable rupture of the lip. Microforms are sometimes associated with disruption of the continuity of the orbicularis oris muscle.

definition.value: Please use this term only when the cleft lip is unilateral, ie occurring only on one side.

value.value: Paladar duro hendido completo
完全な硬口蓋裂
Cleft hard palate in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the hard palate, ie. from the incisor foramen to the anterior border of the soft palate.
Paladar duro hendido incompleto
不完全硬口蓋裂
Cleft hard palate in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the hard palate, ie. the cleft does not go from the incisor foramen to the anterior border of the soft palate.
Paladar blando hendido completo
完全な軟口蓋裂
Cleft soft palate in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the soft palate, i.e. from the posterior border of the hard palate until the uvula.
Paladar blando hendido incompleto
不完全軟口蓋裂
Cleft soft palate in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the soft palate, i.e. the cleft does not go from the posterior border of the hard palate until the uvula.
Cresta alveolar del maxilar hendido incompleto
不完全上顎歯槽堤裂
Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge in which the cleft does not go through the entire length of the maxillary alveolar ridge.
Cresta alveolar maxilar hendida completa
上顎歯槽堤完全裂
Cleft maxillary alveolar ridge in which the cleft goes through the entire length of the maxillary alveolar ridge.

label.value: Complete cleft of the upper lip

value.value: Hendidura completa del labio superior.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Complete cleft of the upper lip

value.value: 完全な上唇裂

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Complete cleft of the upper lip

value.value: Cleft of the upper lip that starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity.

definition.value: If the cleft lip is on only one side, use 'Complete unilateral cleft lip' (HP:5201001). This term was created to be used in association with a left (HP:0012835) or right (HP:0012834) modifier to annotate completeness of a cleft lip.

label.value: Microform cleft of the upper lip

value.value: Microforma de hendidura del labio superior.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Microform cleft of the upper lip

value.value: マイクロフォーム上唇裂

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Microform cleft of the upper lip

value.value: Notch, groove, or scar of the upper lip without noticeable rupture of the lip.

definition.value: If the cleft lip is on only one side, use 'Microform unilateral cleft lip' (HP:5201002). This term was created to be used in association with a left (HP:0012835) or right (HP:0012834) modifier to annotate completeness of a cleft lip.

value.value: Labio hendido bilateral completo
両側完全口唇裂
Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides is complete, i.e. start from the bottom of the upper lip and reach the nasal cavity.
Labio hendido bilateral incompleto
不完全両側口唇裂

Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides are incomplete (i.e. start from the bottom of the upper lip but do not reach the nasal cavity), or the cleft lip on one is incomplete and a microform on the other side.
Microforma de labio hendido bilateral
マイクロフォーム両側口唇裂
Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on both sides are microform, i.e. a notch, groove, or scar without noticeable rupture of the lip.
Labio hendido bilateral asimétrico
非対称性両側口唇裂

Bilateral cleft lip in which the cleft lip on one side is complete (i.e. starts from the bottom of the upper lip and reaches the nasal cavity), and the one on the other side is incomplete (i.e. starts from the bottom of the upper lip but does not reach the nasal cavity) or microform (i.e. a notch, groove, or scar without noticeable rupture of the lip).

definition.value: Consider making additional annotations to specify the type of cleft lip on each side using 'Complete cleft of the upper lip' (HP:5201009), 'Incomplete cleft of the upper lip' (HP:0011340), and/or 'Microform cleft of the upper lip' (HP:5201010).

value.value: Hendidura craneofacial
Congenital abnormality with cleft (gap or opening) in the craniofacial bones. Craniofacial cleft includes facial cleft, orofacial clef, and cleft of the jaw.
Paladar hendido submucoso
A cleft of the muscular portion of the palate that is covered by mucous membrane.
Desorientación izquierda-derecha
A tendency to mix up left and right in one's own body space, typically elicited by asking a person to perform a two-stage command involving specified lateralized anatomy.

definition.value: Some suggest that a tendency to mix up left and right of an examiner's body space is a more reliable feature sensitive.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de proteína DNAJB9 en sangre
Concentration of DnaJ homolog subfamily B member 9 (DNAJB9) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: DNAJB9 is a proteomic tissue biomarker for fibrillary glomerulonephritis.

value.value: Fractura de olécranon
A partial or complete break in the olecranon,which is the proximal articular portion of the ulna and makes up part of the elbow.

definition.value: The olecranon is the proximal articular portion of the ulna. Along with the coronoid process, it forms the greater sigmoid (semilunar) notch which articulates with the humerus to provide flexion and extension of the elbow.

value.value: Antecedentes de mastectomía

definition.value: Past medical history of surgical breast removal.

value.value: Linfangiosarcoma
A malignant neoplasm arising from the endothelial cells of the lymphatic vessels.
Exposición a lípidos inhalados.

definition.value: Aspiration or inhalation of lipid-containing products.

Exogenous lipoid pneumonia is caused by aspiration or inhalation of lipid-containing products. In the past, the most common agents included mineral oil-based laxatives and nasal decongestants. Other causes include inhalation of petroleum jelly used as a lubricant, e.g., tracheostomy care. The incidence of exogenous lipoid pneumonia is growing exponentially in all age groups secondary to the phenomena termed vaping.

value.value: Signo de Holster
Symmetric poikiloderma of hips and lateral thighs below the greater trochanter.

definition.value: The Holster sign may indicate dermatomyositis.

value.value: Adenoma de células basales salivales
A rare neoplasm consisting of a monomorphic population of basaloid epithelial cells, and it accounts for approximately 1-2% of all salivary gland tumors.

definition.value: Thee most frequent location of basal cell adenoma (BCA) of the salivary gland is the parotid gland. It usually appears as a firm and mobile slow-growing mass. Histologically, isomorphic cells in nests and interlaced trabecules with a prominent basal membrane are observed. In contrast to pleomorphic adenoma, it tends to be multiple and its recurrence rate after surgical excision is high.

value.value: Elevación del hemidiafragma

Elevated Hemidiaphragm is a condition where one portion of the diaphragm is higher than the other. Elevated hemidiaphragm occurs when one side of the diaphragm becomes weak from muscular disease or loss of innervation due to phrenic nerve injury.
Nevo de tejido conjuntivo cerebriforme

The cerebriform connective tissue nevus (CCTN) is one of the most characteristic skin findings. It commonly occurs on the soles of the feet, and frequently causes problems because of pain, pruritus, infection, bleeding,exudation, odor, and walking impairment.

definition.value: The cerebriform connective tissue nevus is frequently observed in patients with Proteus syndrome and it is an important specific criterion for diagnosis.

value.value: Hiperpigmentación lineal siguiendo las líneas de Blaschko
Linear streaks and swirls of macular hyperpigmentation along the lines of Blaschko.

definition.value: Blaschko's lines are attributed to the migration lines of epidermal cells during embryogenesis and are characterized by a V-shaped pattern on the posterior midline, S-shape on the abdomen, and spiral on the posterior scalp.

value.value: Culpa excesiva

definition.value: Excessive guilt is an internal feeling that is intense and considered clinically to be beyond normal range, out of proportion for the act or offense; excessive guilt is typically based on an incorrect judgment of responsibility for an unfavorable outcome. Excessive guilt is typically pervasive and enduring, i.e. it is not fleeting or a temporary thought associated with a specific action.

Here we define guilt as the negative feeling that accompanies the belief that one is responsible for a negative outcome or event. Excessive guilt is distinct from self-blame (a cognition/wrong judgment), and rather is defined as excessive given one's perceived responsibility, whether or not the perceived responsibility is accurate.

value.value: Desplazamiento mediastínico

A deviation of the mediastinum from its normal position in the midline of the thoracic cavity. The mediastinum is a compartment of the thoracic cavity that contains the heart and its blood vessels, the esophagus, trachea, thymus, as well as nerves and lymph nodes.

definition.value: Since the pleural cavity is confined by the rib cage, large pleural effusion may push the structures in the thoracic cavity to the opposite side resulting in a shift of the upper and lower mediastinum. Other etiologies are also observed. See Figures 1 and 2 of PMID:35990927 or Figure 1 of PMID:37680422.

value.value: Bendopnea
Dyspnea as a result of bending forward while not holding one's breath; dyspnea or shortness of breath onset within 30 seconds of bending forward.

definition.value: Bendopnea is mediated by increased ventricular filling pressure during bending, which exacerbates an already high filling pressure in patients with heart failure.

value.value: Aumento del dolor al estar acostado
Refers to pain that is worse when the affected individual lies down (flat).
Hipermovilidad de la membrana timpánica
Abnormally increased ability to move of the tympanic membrane.

definition.value: In Stickler syndrome, hypermobility is sometimes associated with thin, visibly hyperflaccid tympanic membranes, which is a common and otoscopically detectable sequela of chronic or recurrent otitis media and/or previous tympanostomy tubes. Hypermobility may also be found with normal appearance tympanic membranes.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de vitamina B12 en sangre
Concentration of vitamin B12 in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: Elevated levels of serum cobalamin may be a sign of a serious, even life-threatening, disease. Hematologic disorders like chronic myelogeneous leukemia, promyelocytic leukemia, polycythemia vera and also the hypereosinophilic syndrome can result in elevated levels of cobalamin.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de FASL soluble en sangre

The concentration of soluble FASL in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal. The first apoptosis signal receptor (FAS) pathway regulates apoptosis and is critical for proper development and functioning of the immune system. FAS ligand (FASL) can bind to FAS receptors.
Acalasia del esfínter anal interno
A disorder of the internal anal sphincter (IAS) in which the IAS fails to relax that manifests clinically as intractable constipation.

definition.value: The internal anal sphincter, which is a specialized smooth muscle continuation of the circular muscle layer of rectum, plays a significant role in the maintenance of anorectal continence and in the pathophysiology of incontinence and constipation. Internal anal sphincter achalasia is a clinical condition with presentation similar to Hirschsprung disease but with the presence of ganglion cells on suction rectal biopsy.

value.value: Exposición a antraciclina

definition.value: History of treatment with an anthracycline chemotherapy agent.

value.value: Consumo excesivo de alcohol

definition.value: A pattern of episodic heavy alcohol use characterized by the consumption of a high number of drinks per occasion.

The World Health Organization defines binge drinking (BD) based on a cut-off of six drinks (i.e., 60g of alcohol) or more per occasion. The National Institute on Alcoholism and Alcohol Abuse (NIAAA) defines BD as a pattern of drinking that brings blood alcohol concentration (BAC) levels to 0.08 g/dL, which typically occurs after 4 drinks (i.e., 56 g of alcohol) for women and 5 drinks (i.e., 70 g of alcohol) for men in about 2 hours.

value.value: Disminución de la concentración de trombopoyetina en sangre

Concentration of thrombopoietin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. Thrombopoietin is a glycoprotein hormone produced by the liver and kidney that stimulates the production and differentiation of megakaryocytes.
Colagenoma

A rare hamartomatous malformation characterized by the predominant proliferation of normal collagen fibers and normal, decreased, or increased elastic fibers. Collagenomas may be solitary or multiple, sporadic, acquired or inherited.
Ausencia de suficiente actividad física diaria.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Lack of sufficient daily physical activity

label.value: Lack of sufficient daily physical activity

value.value: Physical activity levels less than those required for optimal health and prevention of premature death.
Sinestesia

A phenomenon whereby stimulation of one sensory or cognitive pathway leads to automatic, involuntary experiences in a second sensory or cognitive pathway. For instance, people with synaesthesia may experience unusual colors, tastes, and other sensations when engaged in everyday activities like reading or listening to music.
Cerumen oscuro
Abnormally dark color of cerumen (earwax), which is a waxy substance secreted in the ear canal that normally has a brown, orange, red, yellowish or gray.
Historia de ingesta de alimentos picantes.

definition.value: A history of high intake of spciy foods with ingrediaents such as capsaicin, pepper, chili, ginger, garlic, onion, fenugreek, and turmeric.

label.value: Oil-drop brown pigmentation of the corneal limbus

value.value: Pigmentación marrón en forma de gota de aceite del limbo corneal.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Oil-drop brown pigmentation of the corneal limbus

value.value: Brown pigment spots in the limbus (border between the cornea and the sclera).
